  "prompt": "After 22 years my husband wants out and I believe he is seeing someone, but I am still very much in love. How do I get over him? Or win him back?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're going through such a difficult and painful situation. This sounds very challenging. While I can offer some general advice, a professional counselor or therapist might provide the most personalized guidance. Here are some suggestions:\n\nFor healing and moving forward:\n1. Focus on self-care and personal growth\n2. Seek support from friends and family\n3. Consider individual counseling\n4. Allow yourself to grieve the relationship\n5. Stay physically and emotionally healthy\n6. Avoid desperate actions that might push him further away\n\nRegarding potentially reconciling:\n1. Communicate openly and calmly\n2. Listen to his reasons and feelings\n3. Reflect on the relationship's dynamics\n4. Be honest about your own contributions\n5. Consider couples counseling if he's willing\n\nImportant considerations:\n\u2022 If he's truly decided to end the relationship, forcing it won't work\n\u2022 Prioritize your emotional well-being\n\u2022 Be prepared for potential difficult outcomes\n\u2022 Recognize your own worth independent of the relationship\n\nWould you like to discuss any of these points in more detail? Remember that healing takes time, and you're not alone in this process.",
